---
/**
 * Aurora Background Component - Cosmic Ocean Theme v3.1
 *
 * Engineering Note:
 * Pure CSS background animation creates the breathing aurora effect.
 * Multiple large, blurred radial-gradients serve as background layers,
 * driven by @keyframes to move slowly and organically.
 * This achieves an ever-changing, living light effect with minimal performance cost.
 *
 * -z-20 ensures aurora stays behind the starfield canvas (-z-10)
 * opacity-50 dark:opacity-30 makes aurora softer in light mode, subtler in dark mode
 */
---

<div
  aria-hidden="true"
  class="fixed top-0 left-0 w-full h-full -z-20 opacity-50 dark:opacity-30 pointer-events-none"
>
  <div
    class="absolute inset-0 animate-aurora"
    style="
      background-image:
        radial-gradient(ellipse 100% 100% at 50% 50%, rgba(130, 80, 223, 0.3), rgba(13, 17, 23, 0)),
        radial-gradient(ellipse 100% 100% at 50% 50%, rgba(51, 187, 197, 0.3), rgba(13, 17, 23, 0));
      background-size: 200% 200%;
    "
  >
  </div>
</div>
